# 1. 素敵なお誘い

Toya: Where did my phone go...? Ah, it was hiding under my pillow.
Toya: (We're practicing in SEKAI today, but I have a bit of time on my hands. I think I'll head over early and practice on my own until then...)
Toya: Hm? Saki's calling me...? I wonder why...
Saki: <H-Hello, Toya? It's been so long!>
Toya: Good morning, Saki. How can I help you today?
Saki: <So, there's something I wanna talk to you about. Are you free right now?>
Toya: Yes, I have singing practice later today, but we're not meeting for a while.
Saki: <Great! Then...>
Saki: <Have you already heard about the dinner party?>
Toya: Oh, my mom mentioned that to me. Your parents are coming over to my house this Sunday, correct?
Saki: <Yeah, that! Me and Tsukasa got really excited when we heard the news since the last time we had dinner together was forever ago...>
Saki: <But our dad said that it's gonna be adults only, so we can't go...>
Toya: I see. I suppose they have some business they'd like to discuss, but I was also looking forward to having dinner with you and Tsukasa.
Saki: <Me too! But, thank goodness! I knew you'd understand!>
Saki: <So, after talking it over with Tsukasa yesterday, we began thinking about having our own dinner party.>
Saki: <How about it? Wanna come over the Sunday after next?>
Toya: To your house?
Saki: <Yup! Oh, but...it's totally okay if you don't want to...! To be honest, we haven't gotten anything ready yet!>
Toya: The Sunday after next...? I should be free that day, so I'd be more than happy to come over.
Saki: <Really? Woohoo!>
Saki: <Oh, I need to tell Tsukasa the good news! He won't know what to do with himself!>
Toya: Thank you for inviting me. I'll be looking forward to the party.
Saki: <Same! Get ready to be absolutely blown away! Anyway, see you that Sunday! Bye bye!>
Toya: Yes, see you then.
Toya: A dinner party with Tsukasa and Saki at their house...
Toya: (It's been quite a while...)
Toya: (I still remember very vividly how I always seemed to feel at home over there whenever I visited...)
Toya: (Because I never felt all that comfortable in my own home back then...)
Toya: (It happens very rarely these days, but I definitely looked forward to being sent to their house when my parents were busy...)
Toya: And I look forward to seeing them again...
Toya: (I'm still a bit early...)
Toya: For now, I should just head over. We agreed to meet at MEIKO's place as usual...
MEIKO: Oh, Toya, hello. Are you here to practice today?
Toya: Oh, MEIKO...
Toya: Yes, we decided to have practice over here today because it's supposed to rain this afternoon.
Toya: Do you have plans to go somewhere today, MEIKO?
MEIKO: Yes, to where Rin is. I promised her that we'd practice singing together.
Toya: I see. Wait, what about the cafe...?
MEIKO: Oh, about that... I'm lending it out to KAITO and Len for the day.
Toya: Lending it out? What do you mean?
MEIKO: So, the thing is...
Len: Hey, MEIKO! Can we borrow your kitchen for like a day?!
MEIKO: Sure, but... If it's just the kitchen, you can use it right now if you like.
Len: Oh, um... Now would be bad... We need it when no one else is around. In other words, we need the whole cafe to ourselves!
MEIKO: So, what do you plan on doing?
Len: Um, so... That's a secret! Please, I beg you...!
MEIKO: ...is what happened.
Toya: That's an interesting request... Does that mean they're making something they don't want others to see?
MEIKO: Hehe. I suspect so. I mean, I can sort of guess just based on the time of year...
Toya: Hm...? You can?
Toya: Oh, in that case... This means we probably shouldn't try going inside today, yes?
MEIKO: Hmm... I'm not so sure about that.
MEIKO: More specifically, An and Kohane probably are the ones who shouldn't be going in.
MEIKO: You and Akito may actually be welcome.
Toya: Really...?
MEIKO: I'm sure you'll know once you get there. Hehe. In any case, have fun during practice.
Toya: Something they don't want MEIKO and the others to see...
Toya: What in the world could Len and KAITO be making in there...?
